Xinhua Commentary: Make excellent returning migrant workers a force for rural revitalization-Xinhua
Talent is the key to rural revitalization.
Where to find talents?
Excellent migrant workers returning to their hometowns are the indispensable force.
By Shang Haichun, Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The title: Make outstanding returning migrant workers a force for rural revitalization
Zhang Xiong, 34, who lives in Orchard Village, Meishan City, Sichuan Province, quit his job with a monthly salary of tens of thousands of dollars in Beijing in 2010 to start his own business in his hometown.
After a few years of hard work, he now operates a family farm with an annual income of more than one million yuan, and has become a famous wealthy leader, and has been selected to join the village "two committees".
In recent years, in the national poverty alleviation and rural revitalization, a series of policies to support and benefit agriculture have inspired more and more excellent migrant workers like Zhang Xiong to choose to return home and start their own business, activating a pool of spring water in the countryside.
In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries, 61,000 village reserves and more than 20,000 party members have been created from the excellent migrant workers returned to Sichuan, a province with a large population in the west of China and a large labor export province, to take advantage of the situation and implement the "excellent migrant workers return to cultivate project", providing a strong guarantee for winning the battle against poverty and implementing the rural revitalization strategy. This will provide a strong guarantee for winning the battle against poverty and implementing the rural revitalization strategy.
The key to a well-off life depends on the villagers.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and strong laborers in China's rural areas have gone out to work to increase their income, and some of them have started their own enterprises through hard work.
But objectively also led to rural "hollowing out" to varying degrees, especially the weakening of rural grass-roots organizations, the village party branch secretary and party members are showing "an old a low" characteristics, that is, ageing, low education, the village party organization leader team is not strong, and The problem of youthfulness is prominent.
If rural talents and other elements keep flowing to the cities in one direction, the villages will be "bloodless" and "anemic" for a long time, and revitalization is just an empty word.
Attracting those migrant workers who are capable, conscious and interested in serving their hometowns, guiding them to return to their hometowns and become wealthy leaders, and training them as party members and rural cadres on merit to enrich the grassroots cadres, is the fundamental solution to the problem of rural party members and grassroots party organizations.
Excellent migrant workers to attract back, but also to let them stay and do a good job.
In recent years, Sichuan started from the party building of migrant workers, based on the strict criteria of the candidates, the establishment of excellent migrant workers directed back, service protection, training to enhance the ability, selection and use of institutional mechanisms, so that they have the ability to enhance, work on the security, life has the hope, really rooted in the countryside, officers have a sense of achievement in business.
This year is the closing year of the decisive battle against poverty, and talent is the key factor to make a good connection between poverty eradication and rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to the group of excellent returning migrant workers, and through comprehensive measures, make them a task force and a force that can stay, fight and take away, so as to provide strong organizational guarantee and talent support for rural poverty eradication and development revitalization.
