Beijing's natural ecology continues to improve, attracting more than 500 species of wildlife to "settle" in the city - CNN
2020-07-26 05:03:17 Source：Beijing Youth Daily Author：Wang Sishuo Responsibility Editor：Wang Sishuo
The capital's natural ecology continues to improve, attracting wildlife to "settle" in the city
Beijing wildlife has reached more than 500 species
(Reporter Wang Bin) Beijing Youth Daily reporter learned from the Municipal Bureau of Landscaping that in recent years, as the natural ecology of the capital continues to improve, the species and number of wild animals also continue to increase.
At present, the number of terrestrial vertebrate wildlife inhabiting Beijing has increased to more than 500 species, including brown martens, black storks and other national-level protected animals, as well as gazelles, giant swans, gray cranes, mandarin ducks and other national-level protected animals.
Whether it is an urban forest planted in the second ring road or a small wetland embedded between buildings, it not only brings the wildness of nature to the citizens of the capital, but also attracts wild animals to "settle" in the city.
In the summer, the Song Mountain National Nature Reserve in the Yanshan Mountains in the northwest of Yanqing District is a vibrant place.
A raccoon is playing by a mountain stream, while two dog badgers are playing with each other.
A wild boar is rubbing against the bark of a tree, unable to resist the scratching. Hu Qiaoli, director of the Songshan National Nature Reserve Management Office, said that as of the end of 2019, 178 species of wildlife, including national-level protected animals such as golden eagles and second-level protected animals such as spoonbills and gazelles, live in this green sea with a total area of more than 6,200 hectares, and nearly one-third of the city's wildlife species can be found here.
"In Songshan, wild animals are the real 'masters', and our staff can at best be considered as people's 'bodyguards'."
Hu Qiaoli said, in order to understand the situation of wildlife in the reserve, there are more than 30 professional patrol members every day, along 16 carefully developed protection routes, and every month there will be a trip to "turn the big circle", with a full day almost all over the reserve.
"During the patrols, not only do they check and record the biodiversity, but they also check the installation of artificial bird nests, rescue injured wildlife, install infrared cameras in the field, and so on."
The Songshan National Nature Reserve has now installed more than 200 infrared cameras to record the living conditions of wild animals in the forest.
Hu Qiaoli said that as the reserve's biodiversity has been enriched over the past few years, more and more wild animals have appeared on camera, with leopard cats, raccoons and pig badgers becoming "permanent guests" and the "appearance rate" of gazelles, a Grade II protected animal, also increasing.
Zhang Zhiming, Director of the Wildlife and Wetland Protection Division of the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Landscape Architecture, introduced that the number of terrestrial vertebrate wildlife in Beijing has increased from 461 species in 1994 to more than 500 species today, and the number of wildlife species and numbers in Beijing have continued to increase in recent years.
The increasingly common presence of wildlife in the city is closely related to the continuous upgrading of urban greening in the capital in recent years.
In particular, the new round of one million mu of afforestation and greening construction, which began in 2018, proposes to reshape the urban ecological environment, improve the ecological function of woodland green space, and highlight the concept of "near nature".
The planning aims to achieve interconnection and interaction with the surrounding green space, so that wildlife can easily "visit friends and relatives", and the trees planted are the nectar and food source plants that animals love.
Black land "grows" agricultural modernization - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency Harbin, July 26 (Xinhua) - The topic: black land "planting" out of agricultural modernization
In the summer, two spraying planes from the fifth management area of Friendship Farm, the second operating station of 10,000 mu of high-yield demonstration fields swept, forming two white lines, green fields with black rice seedlings planted "the world's first field" a few big words stand out.
This operation station director Kong Lingqiang said, this aircraft can be more than 6,000 acres of arable land spraying agents a day, the efficiency is about 8 times that of the drone, hundreds of times that of manual.
This farm is located in China's first grain-producing province of Heilongjiang Province, Friendship County, from the past "swish" sound of cutting rice through to today's "rumble" of the motor, the Chinese traditional farming and farm in this black soil belt to achieve transformation.
In addition to aircraft, satellites are also used in the modern agricultural production of friendship farms.
Kong Lingqiang introduced, on the one hand, they use satellite remote sensing technology to achieve accurate fertilization, reduce agricultural inputs and pollution; on the other hand, satellite navigation technology can improve the standardization of farm machinery field operations.
In this year's rice production process, the farm will satellite navigation unmanned rice planting technology to expand the operating area from last year's 3,000 mu to 30,000 mu.
This technology enables more uniform planting of seedlings, maximizes the use of sunlight and arable land resources, and saves 16 yuan per mu in labor costs.
The farm tries new technologies such as information technology and intelligence in agricultural production, forming the largest agricultural machinery group in China from the ground to the sky.
According to statistics, the farm currently has a total of 49,000 units (pieces) of agricultural machinery, with a comprehensive mechanization rate of 99.8% in the field.
Agricultural machinery operations achieve 100% GPS satellite navigation, 100% precision sowing in dry fields, and 100% high horsepower locomotive operations in dry fields.
"Green agriculture, intelligent agriculture, digital agriculture is the pathfinding direction of agricultural modernization ."
Youyi Farm Director Liu Hualian said.
The key to modernization of agriculture lies in the progress of science and technology.
Heilongjiang farm as the representative of the farm in recent years to play a large modern agricultural "aircraft carrier" demonstration, leading the role of the initial establishment of large-scale planting, standardized production, industrial operation of the modern agricultural industry system.
In the suburbs of Youyi County, there is an agricultural machinery expo covering an area of 350,000 square meters.
Here is a centralized exhibition of more than 140 (pieces) of agricultural machinery introduced and used by Heilongjiang Nongken over the years.
These farm machinery and farms have witnessed the development of China's agricultural modernization.
