Compared to the Ka-52, the Ka-52M will be partially equipped with new protective materials that do not add weight; its pilot's cockpit will be reinforced and equipped with new equipment to withstand missile attacks, thus increasing the probability of survival on the battlefield; it will be equipped with more powerful generators to power more sophisticated on-board electronics; its electro-optical system will be upgraded to be able to reconnoitre and identify battlefield targets at greater distances; and it will be equipped with major attack The new light multipurpose missile with a range of 20 kilometers, which is about one times longer than the range of the same missile used by Russia's current helicopters, and its defensive weapons and communications equipment will be maximally compatible with the Mi-28NM helicopter gunships, which can attack air targets, making maintenance easy and economical.
In addition, the Ka-52M will have a more advanced electronic guidance system, weapon targeting system and navigation equipment.
Russian experts also said that it is worth noting that the Ka-52M will be equipped with communication equipment for contact with drones, thus obtaining real-time information transmitted from nearby drones in the air, such as displaying images taken by drones on the helicopter's cockpit screen.
It is planned that the pilots of the Ka-52M will be able to directly control the drones that work with them, thus improving the pilots' mastery of the battlefield situation and the guidance of long-range missiles.
According to Russian media reports, Russian Deputy Defense Minister Krivoluchko said in December last year that the Russian Defense Ministry plans to purchase more than 110 armed helicopters Ka-52M by 2027.
