The "south of the border" in pursuit of poetic "Yellow River dream"-China News Network
(China Poverty Reduction Story) "South of the River" pursues poetic "Yellow River Dream"
YINCHUAN, July 26 (Yang Di) - "The nine curves of the Yellow River are ten thousand miles of sand, and the waves and winds have been pounding since the end of the world."
The Yellow River, which has aroused the passions of countless literati, has nurtured the beautiful and fertile Ningxia Plain, and now, Ningxia, which is known as the "South of the River", is adhering to the concept of "ecological priority and green development" and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River Dream". Dream".
The river is clear and beautiful "blue wave dream"
"The Yellow River flows through 397 kilometers of Ningxia, which is the "mother river" that feeds one side.
However, with the rapid progress of industrialization and urbanization, the imbalance between the development and utilization of rivers and lakes and management and protection, excessive discharge, the construction of lakes and fields, encroachment on the waters and other chaotic phenomena, resulting in the black smell of water bodies, water quality exceeds the standard, environmental filth, ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the water ecological diversity restoration, efforts to return the Yellow River water show river clear.
Water treatment to start from the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local adoption of the "standard + pollution + strict control" approach, all industrial parks to achieve centralized treatment of sewage, urban sewage treatment plants to achieve a level A standard discharge, the basic elimination of black smelly water bodies in urban built-up areas, the successful declaration of the third batch of China's black smelly water bodies demonstration cities.
In addition, Ningxia in 2017 to fully implement the river and lake system, now has achieved full coverage of the five levels of the river and lake system responsibility system in the district, city, county and village, the river and lake chief patrol river has become the norm.
Gu Jincheng, 64, lives in a village by the Yellow River, he witnessed the changes in the Yellow River: "The water used to smell bad, after the remediation of the odor is no longer."
Gu Jincheng said, the ecological environment is better, his life is also more comfortable, now he often go for a walk with his family to the Yellow River, feel the blue water and blue sky.
The "wetland dream" of the gull gathering
Birds, green trees, stacks, blue water ...... Fan Zhongyan's "gulls soaring" beauty in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia has become a reality.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia, along the way formed a variety of wetlands such as river wetlands, lake wetlands, marsh wetlands, etc., to promote the rational use of water resources and water ecological balance has an important role, but also become an important international migration channel for birds.
Since 2009, relevant departments in Ningxia have invested a total of about RMB 3.45 billion in wetland protection projects. At present, the wetland area in Yinchuan is 19,200 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%, nearly 200 natural lakes and marsh wetlands, five national wetland parks, one national urban wetland park, six autonomous region level wetland parks and eight municipal parks.
Lv Jinhu, deputy director of the Yinchuan Wetland Protection Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, which is especially evident in birds, "The relic gull is an endangered bird, with only 20,000 or so in the world, of which more than 2,000 inhabit the Yinchuan wetlands."
At the same time, Ningxia according to law on the Yellow River Yinchuan section of the two sides of the wetland protection area delineated a 500-meter interval of the red line, which provides that in addition to public welfare projects, any unit and individual shall not be within the scope of protection of development and construction and business activities.
Yinchuan City, deputy director of the Water Resources Service Center Zhao Shaoyong introduced, through the source of pollution management, comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology and the end of the wetland construction, now Ningxia's nine major drainage ditches into the yellow water quality has reached 100% of the Ⅳ standard, "now the water is also clear, the fish also swim, flowers also bloom."
Universal benefit to the people's livelihood of the "drinking water dream"
Yinchuan City, Ningxia once had an "embarrassing" title: the only city along the Yellow River, the only city "guarding the Yellow River lack of water to drink".
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has been facing a continuous summer peak water shortage problem, nearly a decade of "water shortage pain" has become a lot of high-floor residents summer painful experience, but in the major water sources in the overshoot limit, the urban underground has formed a large area of groundwater overshoot leakage area, water shortage has become a plague Yinchuan City's problem.
Thanks to the improvement of the Yellow River water quality, drinking purified Yellow River water has become a solution to the drinking water problems of local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of the Yinchuan Municipal Water Bureau, introduced that in order to improve the living and production water needs of Yinchuan's urban and rural residents, Ningxia timely launched the Yinchuan Metropolitan Area Urban and Rural Western Water Supply Project, replacing the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River water.
"On December 29, 2019, the water supply project was officially opened to the three districts of Yinchuan City, and in 2020, residents of Minning Town and Helan County also drank Yellow River water . "
Ding Ming said, Yinchuan water conservancy department will coordinate the transformation of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply integration, "the next step, we will integrate the rural scattered water supply points all connected to the western water supply project, is expected to achieve basic urban and rural integrated water supply in the Yinchuan region by the end of this year."
