Speaker of the House Nancy Pelosi (D-Calif.) and Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell (R-Ky.) announced last week that people can pay their respects to Lewis at the U.S. Capitol this Monday and Tuesday.
Because of the coronavirus outbreak, public events to honor Lewis will be held outdoors.
