Tibetan antelopes in Cocosili enter return season - Xinhua

Monitoring images near the Wudaoliang Protection Station show that on July 25, about 40 female Tibetan antelopes led three Tibetan antelope cubs through the Qinghai-Tibet Highway 3002 kilometers and the Qinghai-Tibet Railway Wudaoliang North Bridge one after another, the Tibetan antelopes have begun to return.
According to expert analysis, in recent years, the number of Tibetan antelope cubs in the returning herd accounts for one-fourth to one-fifth of the overall number of Tibetan antelope herd.
Lian Xinming, an associate researcher at the Northwest Plateau Institute of Biology of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, said, "At the beginning of the return migration, Tibetan antelope face a higher risk of predation, so the number of young in the herd will be relatively small, and there may even be no young."
According to the statistics of the Yangtze River Source Park of the Three Rivers National Park Administration, the overall number of Tibetan antelopes returning to the park is rising year by year, with 4,860 Tibetan antelopes returning in 2019, 338 more than in 2018.
Lian Xinming said, "The return migration of Tibetan antelope this year is expected to end in early September, and the number of returning Tibetan antelopes is still expected to continue to increase."
The Tibetan antelope is a national-level protected animal.
At the end of May every year, Tibetan antelopes from the Three Rivers Source in Qinghai, Qiangtang in Tibet, and Arjinshan in Xinjiang are going to lamb at the Zhuo Nai Lake located in the hinterland of Cocosiri.
Wu Xiaomin, an expert in Tibetan antelope conservation in China and a researcher at the Shaanxi Zoological Research Institute (Northwest Institute of Endangered Animals), said, "The return migration of Tibetan antelopes is a process in which female Tibetan antelopes return to their habitat one after another with their young after they have finished giving birth. Initially, the herds that leave their litters are relatively large, but then the Tibetan antelope will return to their respective habitats along different paths, depending on the geographic population."
In order to ensure the safe return of the Tibetan antelope herd, the reporter learned that recently, the Yangtze River Source Park of the Three Rivers National Park Administration has arranged staff in the main return migration area, continuous video monitoring and precinct patrols.
If a Tibetan antelope herd is found trying to cross the highway, patrol members will be the first time to carry out temporary traffic control, so that the flock safely through the wildlife channel to ensure that it is on the way back to the migration as little as possible by human interference.
So, how exactly do you beat the heat in your daily life?
Experts recommend that you try to avoid high temperature periods when you go out in summer. It is best not to walk or work in the hot sun around noon because the sun is strongest during this time and the possibility of heat stroke is higher.
If you must go out at this time, be sure to do a good job of protection, such as playing umbrellas, wearing sun hats, wearing sunglasses, the best conditions to apply sunscreen to prevent sunburn.
Clothes try to use light-colored, breathable cotton, linen, silk texture, less wear chemical fiber clothing, so as not to sweat a lot when the heat can not be timely, causing heatstroke.
High temperature hot weather, to prepare sufficient water to drink in a timely manner, do not wait until thirsty to drink water, because once you feel thirsty that the body has been dehydrated, each drink of water control at 150 ml to 200 ml, drink warm water, do not drink ice water.
According to the temperature, the general staff drink 1.5 liters to 2 liters of water per day, high-temperature workers, drink 3 liters to 5 liters of water per day.
When sweating more can be properly supplemented with some salt water to make up for the salt lost by the body due to sweating.
In addition, the body is prone to potassium deficiency in summer, making people feel tired and weary, potassium tea is an excellent summer drink.
In summer, eat more fruits and vegetables with high water content, such as lettuce, cucumbers, tomatoes, etc.; fresh fruits, such as peaches, apricots, watermelons, melons and other water content of 80% to 90%, can be used to replenish water; dairy products can be hydrated, but also to meet the body's nutritional needs.
In addition, people working in a hot environment should be properly supplemented with drinks containing potassium, magnesium and other elements.
Long days and short nights in summer, high temperatures, the body's metabolism is strong, consumption is also large, easy to feel fatigue.
Adequate sleep can make the brain and body systems are relaxed, both for work and study, is also a measure to prevent heat stroke.
Experts say that the best time to go to bed is 22:00 to 23:00, the best time to get up is 5:30 to 6:30.
Take care not to lie under air conditioning vents and electric fans while sleeping to avoid air conditioning disease and heat stroke.
Experts suggest that people who are active outdoors or working in high temperatures can carry with them heatstroke prevention medicines such as ten drops of water, Ren Dan, patchouli or patchouli pills, or place them in the nearest workplace and use them at any time to prevent heatstroke.
