Beijing, July 26 (Xinhua Gao Kai) July 25 evening, the National Centre for the Performing Arts "sound like summer flowers" series of concerts "Dance of Life" as scheduled online and offline synchronous performance, conductor Yang Yang, pianist Zhang Haochen and the National Centre for the Performing Arts Orchestra Rachmaninoff's Piano Concerto No. 2 and Symphonic Dances were performed on the same stage.
At the same time, the National Centre for the Performing Arts (NCPA) Taiko Theatre, located in the sub-center of Beijing, also welcomed the first offline performance since the fight against the epidemic, with conductor Zheng Jian and the NCPA Chorus singing the "Taiko Week Concert" - Military Choral Song Concert.
After the downgrading of the epidemic response level in Beijing, in accordance with the city's epidemic prevention and control requirements and the spirit of the relevant city departments, the NCPA, in accordance with the principle of "prudent opening and gradual liberalization", the concert performance on July 25, the first limited tickets to the public.
National Centre for theatre marketing minister Jin Hui introduced: "This is the first performance project since the epidemic, the National Centre for theatre tickets to the audience.
According to the epidemic prevention and control-related requirements, the implementation of 'one person, one ticket, one card, one code' of real-name sales and admission, the number of sales does not exceed 30% of the entire seat.
Subsequent performances and art events such as the play "Looking West at Chang'an," a specially planned concert for August 1 Military Day, and an opera film will also be sold to the public in limited numbers."
