(Reporter Yang Zhaokui) The "China Shared Accommodation Development Report 2020" (hereinafter referred to as "the Report") released by the Sharing Economy Research Center of the National Information Center recently shows that the transaction volume of China's shared accommodation market dropped 72.1% year-on-year in the first five months of 2020 due to the impact of the epidemic.
However, the shared accommodation market has been picking up since March, with the market turnover, order volume and number of receptions gradually recovering.
The Report shows that the significant drop in the shared accommodation market transaction volume was due to a sharp drop in order volume due to a significant drop in demand for travel accommodation under the epidemic prevention and control, with the total number of orders in the first five months dropping 65% year-on-year and the number of receptions dropping 63% year-on-year; on the other hand, the weak demand also led to a more significant drop in room night prices, with the average room night price in the first five months dropping 16% year-on-year.
However, market transactions in March, April and May grew 78%, 199% and 35% year-over-year respectively; the number of orders grew 141%, 152% and 50% year-over-year respectively; and the number of receptions grew 81%, 112% and 28% year-over-year respectively.
The Report points out that the development of the shared accommodation industry is promising in the long run, but there are still many uncertainties in the near future.
In this regard, Yu Fengxia, deputy director of the Sharing Economy Research Center of the National Information Center, told the Worker's Daily that the development of shared accommodation needs stronger policy support. On the one hand, it is necessary to do a good job of implementing the policies that have been introduced in the early stage, further strengthen policy dissemination and focus on creating a better business environment; on the other hand, it is also necessary to further stimulate consumer demand, enrich the supply of tourism accommodation services, innovate service methods and On the other hand, it is necessary to further increase the policy guidance and support from various aspects, such as stimulating consumer demand, enriching the supply of tourism accommodation services, innovating service methods and strengthening cooperation between the government and platform enterprises.
