Xiamen, July 26 (Yang Fushan Zhang Shushan Xu Jingyi), China's leading vascular surgery center, the Naval Medical University Shanghai Changhai Hospital vascular surgery, signed a contract with Xiamen University Zhongshan Hospital vascular surgery on the 25th here, to set up a collaborative center to promote the two sides in the vascular surgery specialty, especially the aortic emergency The two sides will promote the exchange and cooperation in the field of vascular surgery, especially in the field of aortic emergencies.
Zhongshan Hospital of Xiamen University said that after the vascular surgery department of the two hospitals formally formed a collaborative unit, they will carry out remote consultation, real-time online consultation with Changhai Hospital to formulate treatment plans, select and send talents for training, and jointly carry out weekly surgical technology exchanges and teaching visits; for complex cases, Changhai experts can be invited to perform surgery in the hospital according to patients' needs, so that patients in southwest Fujian can enjoy top medical resources without leaving the province. The two hospitals will also work together to carry out surgical procedures.
The two hospitals will also work together to carry out innovative scientific research on surgery, popularization of aortic disease and early screening, etc.
A special seminar on aorta was held in Xiamen on the same day, hosted by Beijing Health Promotion Association and organized by Zhongshan Hospital of Xiamen University.
The two well-known hospitals in Shanghai and Xiamen held a signing ceremony for the collaborative center of vascular surgery at the same time, announcing the formation of a collaborative unit to jointly improve the treatment level of vascular surgery-related diseases in southwest Fujian.
Shanghai Changhai Hospital Vascular Surgery Department is the only vascular surgery institute in the army and the only clinical medical center for vascular system diseases in Shanghai, and is also the first national key discipline of vascular surgery, leading the establishment of the Chinese Physicians Association's Professional Committee of Endovascular Angiology, which is a top team with deep accumulation in the industry.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, Director of Vascular Surgery Department of Zhongshan Hospital of Xiamen University, was interviewed by the media.
The Department of Vascular Surgery of Zhongshan Hospital of Xiamen University is the first independent discipline set up in Fujian Province, which has long been dedicated to the diagnosis and treatment of aortic and peripheral vascular diseases and was approved to build a provincial clinical key specialty in 2018.
In the treatment of aortic diseases, it is experienced in emergency ruptured aortic aneurysm, in addition to for the treatment of coarctation aneurysm and aortic aneurysm.
"The vascular surgery department of Zhongshan Hospital of Xiamen University is very outstanding in the region from the history of development, the breadth, difficulty and complexity of surgical operations carried out in many aspects, so this time we set up a collaborative center to carry out all-round in-depth cooperation in medicine, teaching and scientific research in the diagnosis and treatment of lower limb arteries and carotid arteries, in addition to the aorta. "
Professor Feng Rui, deputy director of vascular surgery at Shanghai Changhai Hospital, said.
Zhongshan Hospital of Xiamen University and Shanghai Changhai Hospital had signed a contract in 2018 to establish the "Li Zhaoshen Famous Doctor Studio" in gastroenterology.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, director of the hospital's vascular surgery department, said in an interview with CNN that the hospital's vascular surgery department also has a long history of communication with Changhai Hospital, and the two hospitals have formally formed a collaborative unit to bring their cooperation and communication to a new level.
He said that the hospital will regularly invite Shanghai experts to Xiamen to carry out surgical technology exchange, teaching visits and discussion of difficult cases, while further carrying out remote consultation, which is currently planned to be once a week; in addition, the department will also send personnel for further training and exchange to strengthen the training and development of the discipline's talent team.
The reporter learned at the meeting that vascular disease is the number one cause of death in China, and the aorta plays an important role as the main artery for all organs of the body, flowing from the heart to the whole body.
Aortic disease is often accompanied by high risk, high mortality and high difficulty in treatment. The thickest section of the aorta is 4cm in diameter, and once a hemangioma is formed, a rupture occurs, or the intima ruptures to produce an entrapment, which will cause hemorrhage and is very dangerous.
In recent years, as people's lifestyles have changed and the pace of life has accelerated, China has become the world's largest country in terms of hypertension, and aortic disease has increased. Nowadays, along with the development of surgical techniques and industrial materials, the treatment for aortic disease continues to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
Doctors can "reroute" the blood flow properly by puncturing through the thigh and placing a stent in the aorta, thus avoiding the impact on the aneurysm or ruptured coarctation and achieving a good therapeutic effect, and some procedures even require only local anesthesia.
The symposium invited more than ten domestic experts to discuss new advances in the treatment of aortic disease, and carried out cutting-edge technical training and discussion of difficult cases in the form of a conference salon.
The reporter learned at the meeting that with the development of surgical techniques and industrial materials, the current treatment for aortic diseases continues to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
