Membrane Separation Technology Helps Crack the "Greenhouse Effect"
Schematic diagram of the new hybrid substrate membrane preparation technology
By Shang Rui, reporter: Recently, Tianjin University's atmospheric environment and bioenergy team has made significant progress in "carbon dioxide capture by membrane separation" and successfully developed a new hybrid matrix membrane preparation technology, which significantly improves the carbon dioxide capture performance of membrane materials.
The results were published as the cover article of the international journal "Greenhouse Gases: Science and Technology".
The "greenhouse effect" is a major environmental problem plaguing human development, and CO2 emissions are the culprit of the "greenhouse effect".
How to efficiently capture and utilize human carbon dioxide emissions is the focus of scientists' attention.
"Membrane separation" is a new technology of carbon dioxide capture, which is energy efficient and simple to operate with the help of membrane materials.
How to let the membrane material "breathe" and improve the gas separation efficiency is the bottleneck of carbon dioxide capture by membrane separation method.
The research team of Tianjin University innovated and explored the effect of different solvents on the performance of membrane gas separation through repeated experiments.
The experimental results show that using N-methylpyrrolidone as the preparation solvent, the carbon nanotubes in the generated membrane material are more uniformly distributed and "more breathable", which effectively improves the gas separation efficiency and rate of the membrane material.
The hybrid matrix membranes prepared with this new technology have carbon dioxide separation performance close to the theoretical separation limit of such membrane materials currently available.
"The new technology provides a new idea for carbon dioxide capture by membrane separation."
Li Run, a member of the Atmospheric Environment and Bioenergy team at Tianjin University, said, " We hope this technology will provide strong support for the treatment of flue gas in coal-fired power plants and chemical companies in the future, and play a significant role in areas such as controlling greenhouse gas emissions."
Before filling out the volunteer application, first understand what is the professional level difference - CNN
2020-07-27 02:22:36 Source：Chongqing Morning Post Author：Yu Xiao Responsibility Editor：Yu Xiao
Before filling out the volunteer application, first understand what is the professional grade difference
Every year to fill out the college entrance examination, there are students or parents because of the voluntary application involved in the terminology does not understand, and thus affect the volunteer application.
This year, five universities, including Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University and Beijing University of Chemical Technology, have jointly released their admission policies for 2020, abolishing the professional gradation.
What is the meaning of professional gradation and what is the significance in voluntary application?
There are three ways of professional allocation rules
Experts remind that before filling out the volunteer application, you must read the enrollment prospectus of your preferred school in detail to understand the admission rules of the university, including the transfer ratio and professional allocation rules.
The rules of professional allocation means that after the college transfer, there are mainly three ways of professional priority, score priority and professional level difference for professional admission.
The specific way which colleges and universities use will be clear in the Admission Regulations.
However, there are some colleges and universities whose admission principle is total score priority and no grade difference between majors.
The first one is the first one, and the second one is the second one, and so on until the last one is admitted.
The so-called "professional grade difference", is the institutions in the arrangement of candidates, according to the admissions regulations announced in one or several points value, to determine the admission of different professional volunteer candidates, this score value is the "professional grade difference".
This is the difference between the first and non-first major, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 point, etc.
For example.
Suppose student Xiao Ming applied for college A, scored 560 points, and his major volunteers are: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, e-commerce, and the admission of major in college A is based on the method of major grade difference, which is 2 points, 1 point, 1 point and 0 point.
In the professional allocation, if Xiao Ming's first professional volunteer meets the professional admission requirements and there is a balance of professional plans, then Xiao Ming is admitted to the major of "computer"; if computer is not admitted, then his score will be subtracted by 2 points, and his score will be 558 with the first professional volunteer for " If he still can't meet the requirements, his score will be subtracted by 1 point (i.e. 557 points) and he will be admitted to the third major "Automation"; if he still can't meet the requirements, his score will be subtracted by 1 point (i.e. 556 points) and he will be admitted to the fourth major. If it still can't meet, the score will be reduced by 1 point (i.e. 556 points) for the fourth major.
Different universities set different levels of difference in majors
With the popularity of parallel volunteering, many colleges and universities have abolished the professional grade difference, but this year there are still some colleges and universities still retain this method, from the admissions regulations published by the schools, this year there are mainly more than 20 universities set professional grade difference.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, Civil Aviation Flight Academy of China, etc.
In each of these universities, the level of specialization is set differently.
Some universities have a grade difference in each major, for example, Ningxia University, the file has been cast to the university, according to the order in which candidates fill in the professional volunteers in descending order of 1 point after the score of admission.
And some universities set different professional gradations between different majors.
For example, Jimei University, the total value of the professional volunteer grade difference is 4 points, that is, the first professional volunteer and other professional volunteer grade difference is 3 points, other professional volunteer is not set between the grade difference, as a parallel volunteer, other professional volunteer and transfer professional volunteer professional grade difference is 1 point.
When filling out the volunteer, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policies of the schools they apply to see if there is a professional gradient, what is the form of the gradient, in full consideration of the score, but also a reasonable analysis of the proposed school and professional, if the institution in the admissions regulations clearly take the score gradient way of admission, candidates in the selection of professional, pay attention to the gradient between the professions to improve the chances of admission.
