The scene of the inauguration ceremony of the Dairy Industry Professional Committee taken in Shanghai on July 26.
According to the latest constitution, the exhibition alliance will introduce the lead unit rotation mechanism and strengthen the function of the special committee.
The special committee will make recommendations for the analysis of industry development trends and promote the sustainable development of the industry.
At the same time, it will integrate the resources of the whole industry chain of the industry, bring small enterprises with big ones, drive the related enterprises to exhibit, and make the Fair a highland for industry enterprises to gather.
The establishment of the Public Health Epidemic Prevention Committee for the first time is particularly important for the current fight against the new crown pneumonia epidemic.
As the vice president of the Public Health Epidemic Prevention Committee of the third session of the Fair, Qiu Jianping, general manager of Abbott's rapid diagnostics business in Greater China, said that Abbott will work with more industry partners to explore new solutions and cooperation models to help fight the NCCP epidemic in China and around the world.
The scene of the inauguration ceremony of the Public Health Epidemic Prevention Professional Committee taken in Shanghai on July 26.
It is reported that the Public Health Epidemic Prevention Zone was set up for the first time at the 3rd Fair, and so far nearly 50 global companies have registered to exhibit, with an exhibition area of more than 10,000 square meters.
During the first Fair in 2018, the Fair Exhibitor Alliance was established by exhibitors on their own initiative, aiming to become a platform for exchange and cooperation among high-quality exhibitors, a platform for sharing information and resources connecting exhibitors, and a think-tank platform for promoting economic and trade business exchanges and development between China and other countries (regions) in the world.
So far, 142 enterprises have joined the Exhibitor Alliance, covering 23 countries and regions around the world.
Belgium 3-year-old girl died of new coronavirus infection - Xinhua
Belgian health authorities said on the 24th, a 3-year-old girl died from the new coronavirus infection, is the country's youngest new coronavirus patients died.
Belgian health department spokesman Boudwin Catri said the girl had other serious illnesses before contracting the new coronavirus; in addition to the girl, an 18-year-old youth recently died of the new coronavirus infection.
Catri said 85 percent of the new confirmed cases of New Coronavirus in Belgium last week were under the age of 60.
He cautioned the healthy, younger population not to take it lightly.
"Although it is relatively rare for young people to die from a new coronavirus infection, no one is now immune . "
Last week, Belgium saw an 89 % increase in new confirmed cases of neonatal coronavirus compared to the previous week, with a daily average of 2.9 deaths from neonatal coronavirus infection, up from a daily average of 1.7 in the previous week.
At the peak of the epidemic in Europe, Belgium had the "highest" proportion of people living with NCCV in Europe.
Belgium has a population of more than 11 million.
The latest figures show that a total of 64,847 people in Belgium have been infected with the new coronavirus.
Earlier this week, Cartelli warned that people must act before the snowball grows bigger and eventually causes an "avalanche".
To curb the rebound of the epidemic, Belgian Prime Minister Sophie Vermeers announced on the 23rd that the rules regarding people wearing masks in public places will be stricter, and the program to further lift restrictive measures in August will also be suspended.
