Chengdu People Pile Up Around U.S. Consulate, Police Stop People From "Looking Too Happy"
In response to the U.S. closing the Chinese Consulate General in Houston, China announced the closure of the U.S. Consulate General in Chengdu on Friday.
On Saturday, the emblem was removed from the U.S. Consulate, and on Sunday, a dark glass car drove away from the consulate amid boos from passersby.
On Sunday, many Chengdu residents piled in front of the U.S. Consulate to take pictures, and those who had not been here before came to take a look, driven by curiosity about current events.
AFP Chengdu correspondent also went to Chengdu to observe the vicinity of the U.S. Consulate and reported that there was a steady stream of curious people, as well as many parents who came to walk with their children to see the consulate, take pictures of the building, or take selfies.
The Consulate was surrounded by guards, and police officers occasionally "corrected" people's behavior, seemingly not allowing any out-of-the-ordinary behavior: a woman was stopped just as she was about to sing a red song, and a guard confiscated a banner.
But residents of a nearby residential building managed to pull up a giant Chinese flag on their balcony and shouted pro-China slogans.
The U.S. Consulate in Chengdu, which opened in 1985, covers all U.S. consular-related matters in southwestern China, particularly the Tibet Autonomous Region.
AFP's Chengdu correspondent said that the Chinese government's response to the U.S. has been relatively restrained: many Chinese have called online for the government to close the U.S. consulate in Hong Kong, but officials have simply said that "the closure of the U.S. consulate in Chengdu is a necessary and legal response to unreasonable U.S. behavior.
In addition to Chengdu, the U.S. consulates in China are in Guangdong, Shanghai, Shenyang, Wuhan and Hong Kong.
Large-scale integrated media action "go village live to see the poverty" set off - Today's News - Hunan Daily Online - 华声在线
Hunan Daily - New Hunan Client, July 25 (Our reporter) On July 25, the large-scale integrated media action "Walk the village live to see the poverty" sponsored by the Central Radio and Television Administration's Financial Program Center set off from Xuzhou, Jiangsu Province, and two caravans carrying 5G new media mobile cloud production and broadcasting system slowly drove out of the scene under the eyes of the guests at the scene.
General Secretary Xi Jinping pointed out that "2020 is a milestone year, we will build a moderately prosperous society and achieve the first hundred-year goal, 2020 is also the year of decisive victory in the fight against poverty".
The large-scale integrated media action "Go to the Village Live to See Poverty Eradication" is an important initiative of the Financial Program Center of China Central Radio and Television to match this major theme and do a good job in promoting poverty eradication.
The action will go to the villages in more than 20 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the central government to dig out the vivid stories of poverty eradication, to hit the dramatic changes of village appearance, and to show how the villagers break through the difficulties of survival and development and go to the road of prosperity.
This operation will last for more than 3 months.
Reporters from Xuzhou, divided into two ways, all the way to the southwest line, through Anhui, Hubei, Jiangxi, Hunan, Guangxi, Guizhou, Sichuan, Chongqing, Yunnan, Tibet and other places; the other way to the northwest line, through Henan, Shaanxi, Gansu, Qinghai, Xinjiang, Ningxia, Inner Mongolia, Shanxi, Hebei and other places, the journey of more than 10,000 kilometers.
In the form of reporting, "go live to see the village out of poverty" bold integration.
The economic development of the villages visited by the caravan will be broadcasted through CCTV financial channel, CCTV Economic Voice, China Traffic Radio and CCTV Financial New Media.
Among them, the live TV broadcast will be done mainly on CCTV Finance Channel's midday news program "World Finance" (first broadcast time: 12:00-13:00 from Monday to Sunday), and CCTV Finance Channel's prime-time news column "Economic Information" will open a column on poverty eradication (first broadcast time: 20:30-21:30 from Monday to Sunday).
At the same time, the caravan will broadcast live for up to one hour in the CCTV Finance client for each village it visits, and viewers can watch the live broadcast and participate in the lottery by downloading the CCTV Finance APP.
In terms of technology application and studio design, "Live Village Watching Poverty Alleviation" has made a breakthrough and created the first "Outfield New Media Caravan".
The car is equipped with 5G new media mobile cloud production and broadcasting system, using 5G+4K/8K+AI technology to realize the organic combination of online and offline, large and small screens, and TV broadcasting.
Configured with three news broadcast area, the broadcast area is converted from a container, 12 meters long, 2.55 meters wide, 3.98 meters high, the box adopts hydraulic automatic unfolding structure, the maximum can be turned up 120 degrees.
The broadcast area can also be automatically unfolded, and external expansion platform, an area of more than 50 square meters, can meet the requirements of most of the program scenes.
Right now, it is already a hot summer day in Dongchuan District, Kunming, and what is hotter than the weather is the poverty alleviation workshop next to the relocation site.
Lv Ling, an employee of Kunming Asford Electronic Technology Company, said, "Now, once out of the house, into the factory door, making money and caring for the family, thanks to the free vocational skills training organized by the trade union."
Into the Dongchuan District Tongdu Street electronic components processing workshop to alleviate poverty, a hot and busy picture into the eyes.
More than 40 years old Lv Ling is a single mother, a person with children, but also to take care of elderly parents.
In her most difficult time, Dongchuan District Federation of Trade Unions to help come up with ideas and solutions, and run before and after the "charcoal in the snow".
Since 2018, Lv Ling has enjoyed housing, schooling, social security, employment and other support policies and support money issued by trade unions at all levels.
This year, her children have successfully graduated and employed, and she herself has got a job and income after participating in skills training, and got out of trouble at the end of April.
It is reported that the Dongchuan District General Organization to help poverty alleviation special skills training project, is part of the Yunnan Provincial Federation of Trade Unions skills training work.
The district federation combined with the characteristics of the difficult workers in the district's relocation site for poverty alleviation, in-depth investigation to understand the training needs, determine the training types, the recent plan to train a total of 450 electricians, welders, pastry chefs, etc.
Recently, Li Yi, an employee of Agricultural Bank of Yunnan Menglian County Branch, wrote a heartfelt letter of thanks to the County Federation of Trade Unions.
In the letter, she sincerely thanked the trade union for the Golden Autumn Scholarship given to her between August 2013 and January 2017 to help her complete her education.
In 2004, Li Yi's father died in a car accident and her mother was included in the file of difficult workers, and since then, she has been enjoying the care of the file-building policy.
With the help of the local labor union, Li Yi successfully completed her education.
Since 2016, 3,809 households have been released from hardship through institutional protection and precise help.
The successful relief of Lv Ling's family and Li Yi is a microcosm of Yunnan trade unions' work to promote the relief of difficult workers.
According to Duan Kaiyuan, a staff member of the Legal and Rights Protection Department of the Yunnan Federation of Trade Unions, the provincial federation has strengthened the dynamic management of difficult workers' files, promoted the normalization of file building, and promptly included difficult workers who meet the file building conditions into the help system; broadened the application channels for difficult workers, and used WeChat to open an online application service platform for difficult workers' file building, so that difficult workers can take the initiative to declare in time.
During the epidemic, it was difficult to go out to work. In order to help the workers in difficulty in the file to relieve the pressure of life, the Yunnan Provincial Federation arranged more than 13 million yuan of warmth funds to implement special warmth sympathy activities for more than 6,000 national and 1,000 provincial workers in difficulty in the file according to the standard of 2,000 yuan per household for workers in difficulty in the national level and 1,500 yuan per household for workers in difficulty in the provincial level.
At the same time, the provincial federation dovetailed with human resources and social departments and various Internet recruitment platforms such as Wise-Links Recruitment to push recruitment information to workers in difficulty and provide employment consultation, employment guidance and other services.
